1
00:00:15,333 --> 00:00:16,567
Sorry, Yen.

2
00:00:16,633 --> 00:00:18,567
I'm not taking
advantage of you.

3
00:00:18,633 --> 00:00:20,133
It was my first kiss.

4
00:00:20,200 --> 00:00:21,467
I'm embarrassed.

5
00:00:21,533 --> 00:00:26,467
Because it's only now that I get
to experience these things.

6
00:00:26,533 --> 00:00:28,267
I'm so lucky.

7
00:00:28,333 --> 00:00:29,233
You didn't just save me.

8
00:00:29,300 --> 00:00:31,100
I was also your first kiss.

9
00:00:31,167 --> 00:00:34,100
Thank you for
staying by my side.

10
00:00:34,200 --> 00:00:36,100
I will never leave you too.

11
00:00:36,167 --> 00:00:39,367
And I will never let the
two of us be separated.

12
00:00:39,433 --> 00:00:42,633
I don't understand why
this is happening to us!

13
00:00:42,700 --> 00:00:44,433
We're good people!

14
00:00:44,500 --> 00:00:46,400
Actions speak
louder than words.

15
00:00:46,467 --> 00:00:47,733
What are you trying to say?

16
00:00:47,800 --> 00:00:49,367
What was Zandro doing here?

17
00:00:49,433 --> 00:00:53,100
And I hate to say this,
but whenever I see you

18
00:00:53,167 --> 00:00:55,333
and your brother talking, I feel
you're doing something shady.

19
00:00:55,400 --> 00:00:57,467
My mom used to be like that too.

20
00:00:57,533 --> 00:01:01,000
Whenever we get
hurt from playing,

21
00:01:01,067 --> 00:01:03,267
she kisses our wounds.

22
00:01:03,333 --> 00:01:08,567
Whenever you remember your
mom, you're both happy and sad.

23
00:01:08,667 --> 00:01:11,467
Ever since my older
brother died....

24
00:01:11,533 --> 00:01:13,833
Why did your brother die?

25
00:01:13,900 --> 00:01:15,767
He was killed.

26
00:01:15,833 --> 00:01:17,667
I'm sorry, Dindi.

27
00:01:17,733 --> 00:01:20,533
Your contract won't be renewed.

28
00:01:20,600 --> 00:01:21,700
What?

29
00:01:21,767 --> 00:01:25,900
To remind us that we will
never leave each other.

30
00:01:25,967 --> 00:01:29,500
I promise upon the plants...

31
00:01:29,567 --> 00:01:30,933
the sea...

32
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:32,100
the rain...

33
00:01:32,167 --> 00:01:33,800
that these shells will...

34
00:01:33,867 --> 00:01:35,767
bind us together...

35
00:01:35,833 --> 00:01:37,167
forever.

36
00:01:43,133 --> 00:01:47,833
I need to find a new
job because I'm broke.

37
00:01:47,900 --> 00:01:52,700
I used my savings
to pay for our rent.

38
00:01:52,767 --> 00:01:54,033
What do we do now?

39
00:01:54,100 --> 00:01:55,300
I'm sorry, Dindi.

40
00:01:55,367 --> 00:01:57,500
I can't help but think

41
00:01:57,567 --> 00:01:59,933
that you're going through
this because of me.

42
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:01,333
Don't think that way.

43
00:02:01,400 --> 00:02:02,533
I get it.

44
00:02:02,600 --> 00:02:03,400
I understand.

45
00:02:03,467 --> 00:02:04,500
No!

46
00:02:04,567 --> 00:02:07,567
I have a feeling that
this is all Rina's doing.

47
00:02:07,633 --> 00:02:10,600
She gives hell to all
the people close to me.

48
00:02:10,667 --> 00:02:12,967
She's so evil!

49
00:02:14,467 --> 00:02:15,500
Such a pest!

50
00:02:20,633 --> 00:02:22,333
I know...

51
00:02:27,067 --> 00:02:30,900
I know this is not the right
time to tell you how I feel,

52
00:02:30,967 --> 00:02:33,000
but...

53
00:02:33,067 --> 00:02:33,867
when will I do that?
Right?

54
00:02:36,067 --> 00:02:38,833
Our life here is
full of uncertainty.

55
00:02:40,233 --> 00:02:43,733
We need to make
the most out of...

56
00:02:43,800 --> 00:02:45,500
every minute...

57
00:02:47,700 --> 00:02:49,100
every second.

58
00:02:53,267 --> 00:02:57,000
Because we don't know what can
happen tomorrow.

59
00:03:00,367 --> 00:03:02,400
There's only one
thing I'm sure about.

60
00:03:04,167 --> 00:03:07,633
What's important to me
right now,

61
00:03:07,700 --> 00:03:10,833
is my feelings for you.

62
00:03:14,200 --> 00:03:15,700
Yen...

63
00:03:17,733 --> 00:03:19,200
I like you.

64
00:03:26,900 --> 00:03:28,867
You know what, Red...

65
00:03:30,900 --> 00:03:34,067
When you almost died,

66
00:03:34,133 --> 00:03:36,167
I thought I would go crazy.

67
00:03:39,467 --> 00:03:42,633
That's when I realized
that you're important to me.

68
00:03:42,700 --> 00:03:46,867
I didn't know why
I felt like that.

69
00:03:46,933 --> 00:03:48,133
I thought...

70
00:03:49,433 --> 00:03:51,367
I thought I was just
scared to be alone.

71
00:03:54,367 --> 00:03:56,433
But now everything
is clear to me.

72
00:03:58,267 --> 00:03:59,800
I like you too.

73
00:07:47,700 --> 00:07:48,733
Come on, Rina.

74
00:07:48,833 --> 00:07:50,933
Don't you trust me?

75
00:07:51,000 --> 00:07:54,033
Josie told me that she
had already fired Dindi.

76
00:07:54,100 --> 00:07:57,000
I just want to make sure.

77
00:07:58,933 --> 00:08:00,033
There they are.

78
00:08:08,067 --> 00:08:09,167
Amanda!

79
00:08:17,433 --> 00:08:19,333
Amanda!

80
00:08:24,667 --> 00:08:27,867
That's what you deserve.

81
00:08:27,933 --> 00:08:29,633
Filth begets filth.

82
00:08:29,700 --> 00:08:33,800
But you're filthier than that
mud because you're a murderer!

83
00:08:33,867 --> 00:08:34,600
A criminal!

84
00:08:34,667 --> 00:08:36,933
You're so evil!

85
00:08:37,000 --> 00:08:38,833
You should not involve
my sister in this!

86
00:08:38,900 --> 00:08:40,700
She lost her job
because of you!

87
00:08:40,767 --> 00:08:43,200
Well, I'm just starting!

88
00:08:43,267 --> 00:08:44,800
She didn't do anything wrong.

89
00:08:44,867 --> 00:08:45,600
No.

90
00:08:45,667 --> 00:08:47,700
Your clan will
feel my wrath!

91
00:08:47,767 --> 00:08:51,333
Even your daughter
if she's alive.

92
00:08:51,400 --> 00:08:54,167
This mud is as
dirty as your mouth!

93
00:08:54,267 --> 00:08:55,167
I don't think so.

94
00:08:55,233 --> 00:08:56,900
You and that mud are
of the same kind!

95
00:08:56,967 --> 00:08:58,567
There is no difference.

96
00:08:58,633 --> 00:08:59,667
Oh, really?

97
00:09:02,300 --> 00:09:03,267
Oh my god!

98
00:09:04,300 --> 00:09:06,367
How dare you, Amanda!

99
00:09:07,067 --> 00:09:08,333
Amanda! Stop it!

100
00:09:08,400 --> 00:09:09,200
Amanda!

101
00:09:09,267 --> 00:09:11,633
If I'm a mud, then
you're a spit!

102
00:09:11,700 --> 00:09:13,000
Now that's what you
call no difference!

103
00:09:13,067 --> 00:09:14,567
You witch!

104
00:09:14,633 --> 00:09:15,433
Amanda!

105
00:09:17,167 --> 00:09:18,433
Amanda, that's enough!

106
00:09:18,500 --> 00:09:19,367
Stop it!

107
00:09:19,433 --> 00:09:20,700
- You beast!
- Stop it! That's enough!

108
00:09:20,767 --> 00:09:21,367
Amanda!

109
00:09:21,433 --> 00:09:24,833
Amanda! That's enough!

110
00:09:24,900 --> 00:09:25,667
Amanda!

111
00:09:25,733 --> 00:09:27,833
- Stop!
- Stop! Amanda, stop it!

112
00:09:27,933 --> 00:09:28,867
What's wrong with you!

113
00:09:30,667 --> 00:09:31,233
Rina!
I'm warning you, Amanda!

114
00:09:32,167 --> 00:09:34,167
I'm not done with you yet!

115
00:09:34,233 --> 00:09:35,867
Pray that your daughter
is already dead!

116
00:09:35,933 --> 00:09:39,267
So she won't
feel my wrath!

117
00:09:39,333 --> 00:09:41,067
Remember this, Amanda.

118
00:09:41,133 --> 00:09:43,667
No one escapes my wrath!

119
00:09:43,733 --> 00:09:44,500
Brace yourself!

120
00:09:44,567 --> 00:09:47,100
I'm not scared of
your darn wrath!

121
00:09:47,167 --> 00:09:48,000
Beast!
- Let's go!
 - I'll spit at you!

122
00:09:49,000 --> 00:09:50,433
Monster!

123
00:09:50,500 --> 00:09:51,133
Go on! Get in!

124
00:09:51,200 --> 00:09:52,533
Let's go!

125
00:09:55,500 --> 00:09:56,700
Arrogant!

126
00:09:57,567 --> 00:09:58,600
Ugly!

127
00:10:01,400 --> 00:10:04,467
Come on!

128
00:10:07,267 --> 00:10:08,600
Fight me!

129
00:10:30,600 --> 00:10:32,033
Thank you, Yenyen.

130
00:10:34,567 --> 00:10:41,400
You made me happy
amid uncertainty.

131
00:10:43,333 --> 00:10:45,833
Thanks to you, too, Red.

132
00:10:45,900 --> 00:10:50,433
You erased my
fears and doubts.

133
00:10:52,033 --> 00:10:53,967
I feel more secure.

134
00:10:57,467 --> 00:10:58,600
You know what?

135
00:11:01,167 --> 00:11:02,967
When we return to Manila,

136
00:11:05,133 --> 00:11:07,633
I will introduce you
to my parents.

137
00:11:09,833 --> 00:11:14,300
I will tell them
you're the woman...

138
00:11:15,800 --> 00:11:18,000
who cared for me.

139
00:11:19,267 --> 00:11:20,767
The woman I like.

140
00:11:22,300 --> 00:11:23,467
Me, too.

141
00:11:24,567 --> 00:11:26,833
I will introduce
you to my mom.

142
00:11:26,900 --> 00:11:32,200
I will tell her that a kind
and good-looking prince charming

143
00:11:32,267 --> 00:11:34,633
took care of me on this island.

144
00:11:40,700 --> 00:11:43,733
Do you think your
mother will like me?

145
00:11:43,800 --> 00:11:45,233
Of course.

146
00:11:45,300 --> 00:11:46,733
My mom is kind.

147
00:11:50,333 --> 00:11:55,667
Do you think your parents
will like me, Red?

148
00:11:58,100 --> 00:11:59,833
We're not well-off.

149
00:12:01,467 --> 00:12:02,733
And my mom went to jail.

150
00:12:02,800 --> 00:12:04,633
Don't be negative.

151
00:12:07,267 --> 00:12:12,800
I'm sure they will understand
my feelings for you.

152
00:12:13,933 --> 00:12:15,733
They will respect it.

153
00:12:30,467 --> 00:12:32,233
Hell no!

154
00:12:32,300 --> 00:12:34,633
I don't regret what I did.

155
00:12:35,333 --> 00:12:38,800
The mud isn't
enough for Amanda.

156
00:12:38,867 --> 00:12:41,900
Didn't I tell you
to leave them be?

157
00:12:41,967 --> 00:12:44,200
Why are you so stubborn?

158
00:12:44,267 --> 00:12:47,867
And why did you have to
involve Amanda's sister?

159
00:12:47,967 --> 00:12:50,333
She didn't do us wrong.

160
00:12:50,400 --> 00:12:53,833
Well, she's unlucky
to be Amanda's sister.

161
00:12:53,900 --> 00:12:55,800
Rina, you're hurting
other people too.

162
00:12:55,867 --> 00:12:58,067
Why? Hold on, Victor!

163
00:12:59,400 --> 00:13:00,333
Are they the only
ones who got hurt?

164
00:13:00,400 --> 00:13:02,067
Was I not hurt?

165
00:13:04,033 --> 00:13:05,767
When Angelo died,

166
00:13:07,133 --> 00:13:08,600
it was not just painful.

167
00:13:08,667 --> 00:13:10,667
I wasn't just hurt.

168
00:13:10,733 --> 00:13:12,800
It's like I
was killed too!

169
00:13:15,233 --> 00:13:17,600
And it's all
because of Amanda!

170
00:13:17,667 --> 00:13:19,967
She deserves to suffer!

171
00:13:22,233 --> 00:13:23,800
And now what?

172
00:13:25,200 --> 00:13:26,867
Red is missing.

173
00:13:28,567 --> 00:13:31,067
Are we childless now?

174
00:13:31,133 --> 00:13:32,300
Did we already lose
both our children?

175
00:13:32,367 --> 00:13:36,000
Tell me, Victor!

176
00:13:36,067 --> 00:13:39,767
Everyone dear to
me is all gone!

177
00:13:39,833 --> 00:13:44,733
They're gone!

178
00:13:51,733 --> 00:13:53,567
Stop crying.

179
00:13:53,633 --> 00:13:56,500
You have to let go.

180
00:13:56,600 --> 00:13:59,867
I know there's no forgiveness
for what Amanda did to us.

181
00:13:59,933 --> 00:14:01,867
We both hate her.

182
00:14:03,533 --> 00:14:06,433
But we have to do
the right thing.

183
00:14:10,033 --> 00:14:12,200
Let's take care of Red first.

184
00:14:13,867 --> 00:14:15,533
Stop living in the past.

185
00:14:16,900 --> 00:14:18,700
Red needs us.

186
00:14:27,600 --> 00:14:29,100
That Rina is a beast!

187
00:14:29,167 --> 00:14:30,967
She's so evil!

188
00:14:33,767 --> 00:14:38,767
Amanda, evil will never win.

189
00:14:38,833 --> 00:14:40,933
Aren't they winning, Dindi?

190
00:14:41,000 --> 00:14:46,033
Didn't everything that happened
to me show that evil wins?

191
00:14:46,100 --> 00:14:50,067
God has reasons
we don't know.

192
00:14:50,133 --> 00:14:54,233
For me, God was sleeping
when I went to jail.

193
00:14:54,300 --> 00:14:56,533
He abandoned me.

194
00:14:56,600 --> 00:14:58,767
I hope he wakes up this time

195
00:14:58,833 --> 00:15:02,167
and let me be with
my daughter again.

196
00:15:02,267 --> 00:15:04,633
I just want to live
for my daughter.

197
00:15:04,700 --> 00:15:07,300
I want to start a new
life for her sake.

198
00:15:07,367 --> 00:15:11,533
I want to give
her the best.

199
00:15:11,600 --> 00:15:14,933
God is generous, Amanda.

200
00:15:15,000 --> 00:15:18,933
I believe that we
will still see Yenyen.

201
00:15:19,000 --> 00:15:23,067
And she will be
happy to see you.

202
00:15:23,133 --> 00:15:24,933
She'll be proud of you.

203
00:15:25,000 --> 00:15:28,267
I'm sure that we will
be a happy family again.

204
00:15:56,000 --> 00:15:57,167
Here.

205
00:16:14,433 --> 00:16:15,467
Are you okay?

206
00:16:17,300 --> 00:16:18,533
My mom.

207
00:16:23,100 --> 00:16:25,200
I don't know what's
happening to her right now,

208
00:16:25,267 --> 00:16:27,200
but...

209
00:16:29,233 --> 00:16:32,567
I'm getting
worried for her.

210
00:16:32,633 --> 00:16:34,600
I miss her, Red.

211
00:16:37,100 --> 00:16:38,133
Don't worry.

212
00:16:40,000 --> 00:16:43,367
Let's just gather
sticks and logs,

213
00:16:43,467 --> 00:16:45,200
and we'll get the raft done.

214
00:16:48,300 --> 00:16:51,533
We will be with our
family again.

215
00:16:51,600 --> 00:16:53,233
We'll go home.

216
00:16:55,433 --> 00:16:57,100
We get to hug them.

217
00:17:00,700 --> 00:17:01,867
I promise.

218
00:18:48,733 --> 00:18:49,767
Ready?

219
00:18:49,833 --> 00:18:51,367
Ready!

220
00:18:51,433 --> 00:18:52,267
Rain or shine?

221
00:18:52,333 --> 00:18:54,600
Rain or shine!

222
00:18:54,700 --> 00:18:56,300
This won't be easy.

223
00:18:56,367 --> 00:18:58,000
I know.

224
00:18:58,067 --> 00:19:02,233
But remember, never give up!

225
00:19:02,300 --> 00:19:03,400
- Come on.
- Let's go.

226
00:20:26,667 --> 00:20:28,033
Why are you up so early?

227
00:20:28,100 --> 00:20:29,700
The sun hasn't risen yet.

228
00:20:29,767 --> 00:20:32,500
I'm going to apply for a job.

229
00:20:32,567 --> 00:20:34,600
My former colleague
recommended me.

230
00:20:34,700 --> 00:20:35,933
It's too far.

231
00:20:36,000 --> 00:20:38,200
I might get stuck in traffic.

232
00:20:38,267 --> 00:20:40,667
I'm sure you'll get
the job because you're good

233
00:20:40,733 --> 00:20:43,233
and you're good at
dealing with people.

234
00:20:43,300 --> 00:20:44,167
I hope so.

235
00:20:44,233 --> 00:20:46,067
Please pray for me.

236
00:20:46,133 --> 00:20:48,333
You're always in my prayers.

237
00:20:48,400 --> 00:20:50,200
You and Yenyen.

238
00:20:50,267 --> 00:20:51,933
Thank you, Amanda.

239
00:20:52,000 --> 00:20:54,633
Be safe too, when you
sell those rice cakes.

240
00:20:54,700 --> 00:20:57,233
There are a lot
of crooks out there.

241
00:20:57,300 --> 00:20:59,733
You, too. Be safe.

242
00:20:59,800 --> 00:21:01,200
I hope I can
sell all these.

243
00:21:01,267 --> 00:21:04,067
So I can give back
the money you lent me.

244
00:21:04,133 --> 00:21:05,567
You will. I'm sure of it.

245
00:21:05,633 --> 00:21:07,933
Just stay positive.

246
00:21:08,000 --> 00:21:10,200
I want to be positive
all the time.

247
00:21:10,300 --> 00:21:12,733
But because of people
like Rina,

248
00:21:12,800 --> 00:21:15,267
you can't help
but become negative.

249
00:21:15,333 --> 00:21:18,533
I want to ignore her.

250
00:21:18,600 --> 00:21:21,400
But I can't help it

251
00:21:21,467 --> 00:21:27,833
whenever she does something
wrong to you and Yenyen.

252
00:21:30,167 --> 00:21:33,500
I'd been to jail, Dindi.

253
00:21:33,567 --> 00:21:37,267
I saw how dark it was.

254
00:21:37,333 --> 00:21:38,333
I got used to it.

255
00:21:38,400 --> 00:21:40,700
So I'm not scared
to go back to jail

256
00:21:40,767 --> 00:21:43,633
once they do something wrong
to my loved ones.

257
00:21:43,733 --> 00:21:48,867
My life would be meaningless
if not for you and Yenyen.

258
00:21:48,933 --> 00:21:51,033
I'm a good person.

259
00:21:51,100 --> 00:21:54,100
But they will trample on you
if you're a good person.

260
00:21:54,167 --> 00:21:56,667
They will just
kick you off.

261
00:21:56,733 --> 00:21:58,867
Just hang in
there, Amanda.

262
00:21:58,933 --> 00:22:02,600
There are more good
people in this world.

263
00:22:02,667 --> 00:22:04,900
There are only
a few bad ones.

264
00:22:04,967 --> 00:22:09,333
Let's just pray that God
will protect us against them.

265
00:22:09,400 --> 00:22:12,167
And because you're
a good person,

266
00:22:12,233 --> 00:22:15,000
I'm sure you'll sell everything.

267
00:22:15,100 --> 00:22:17,400
All of that.

268
00:22:17,467 --> 00:22:18,433
That's what I
like about you.

269
00:22:18,500 --> 00:22:19,500
You always have
good vibes.

270
00:22:19,567 --> 00:22:20,500
Everything will be sold.
- Promise.
- That's good.

271
00:22:21,567 --> 00:22:22,700
Keep going.

272
00:22:22,767 --> 00:22:23,567
Perfect.

273
00:22:23,633 --> 00:22:24,633
It smells good.

274
00:22:24,700 --> 00:22:26,067
Perfect.

275
00:22:29,067 --> 00:22:32,333
Red and I are
going home, coach.

276
00:22:35,733 --> 00:22:38,500
This is what you
want for us, right?

277
00:22:40,267 --> 00:22:42,467
To get back home safely.

278
00:22:46,667 --> 00:22:49,867
I'm just sad that...

279
00:22:49,967 --> 00:22:52,467
you won't be with us.

280
00:22:58,100 --> 00:22:59,933
I will miss you, coach.

281
00:23:04,267 --> 00:23:06,600
I don't have a
mentor anymore.

282
00:23:11,433 --> 00:23:14,600
No one will
reprimand me anymore.

283
00:23:24,100 --> 00:23:25,467
Coach,

284
00:23:27,467 --> 00:23:30,800
I will remember all the...

285
00:23:32,267 --> 00:23:34,600
things you taught me.

286
00:23:37,500 --> 00:23:41,033
All the good moments
you shared with me.

287
00:23:46,067 --> 00:23:47,700
And coach...

288
00:23:50,200 --> 00:23:53,133
I will give this
to your daughter.

289
00:23:53,200 --> 00:23:54,367
I promise, coach.

290
00:23:58,467 --> 00:24:00,867
I love you so much.

291
00:24:13,233 --> 00:24:15,533
Coach...

292
00:24:15,600 --> 00:24:20,700
For the brief moment
that I spent with you...

293
00:24:20,767 --> 00:24:23,500
I saw how good a
person you are.

294
00:24:26,133 --> 00:24:29,967
And I felt how much you loved

295
00:24:30,067 --> 00:24:32,033
and treated Yenyen
like your child.

296
00:24:36,933 --> 00:24:40,533
Coach, I promise we'll
get out of this island.

297
00:24:43,700 --> 00:24:47,000
Thank you so much...

298
00:24:47,067 --> 00:24:48,900
for the hope.

299
00:24:50,300 --> 00:24:53,067
Thank you for the courage,

300
00:24:53,133 --> 00:24:54,700
you've given us.

301
00:24:58,067 --> 00:25:03,133
We have a lot of memories
on this island.

302
00:25:03,233 --> 00:25:04,800
Sad...

303
00:25:05,933 --> 00:25:07,767
scary.

304
00:25:09,733 --> 00:25:11,667
It brought helplessness.

305
00:25:14,133 --> 00:25:19,767
But I forgot all of it
when I met Yenyen.

306
00:25:24,733 --> 00:25:26,533
By the way, coach.

307
00:25:28,300 --> 00:25:32,067
I'm also asking for your
blessing for our relationship.

308
00:25:36,467 --> 00:25:40,600
I promise I won't
make her cry.

309
00:25:40,667 --> 00:25:44,400
Haunt me if I do that.

310
00:26:06,033 --> 00:26:06,933
Yen, there are rocks!

311
00:26:07,000 --> 00:26:08,333
Hold on tight!

312
00:26:09,133 --> 00:26:10,200
Yen!

313
00:26:11,167 --> 00:26:14,800
Sir Victor, there are remains
found from the plane crash.

314
00:26:14,867 --> 00:26:16,733
They were students
from your son's school.

315
00:26:16,800 --> 00:26:18,133
Is it Red?

316
00:26:18,200 --> 00:26:19,233
My son?

317
00:26:19,300 --> 00:26:20,300
Miss?

318
00:26:24,867 --> 00:26:25,167
Come here.

319
00:26:25,267 --> 00:26:26,967
Oh my god!

320
00:26:27,033 --> 00:26:28,467
Rina, you might
not bear the news.

321
00:26:28,533 --> 00:26:30,633
Victor, please!

322
00:26:30,700 --> 00:26:32,833
I cannot wait any longer.

323
00:26:32,900 --> 00:26:37,833
I've been wanting to know
what happened to our son.

324
00:26:37,900 --> 00:26:40,200
There's an unidentified man.

325
00:26:40,267 --> 00:26:41,367
Here he is, Ma'am.
